        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 2:52PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 31
miles east of Ranch Campground, or 32 miles east of Ursine, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Iron
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
